quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,43,"And never did We send as messengers before you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>except men to whom <span class=""h"">We reveal<sup foot_note=""80388"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>. So ask<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>the people of the Reminder if you do not know."
  16,44,"<i class=""s"">(We sent them) </i>with evident proofs and books. And We sent down to you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>the Reminder, that you may clarify to mankind what was bestowed upon them from on high, and that they may reflect."
  16,45,"Do those who have schemed evils feel secure that Allah will not cause the earth to cave in beneath them, or that the punishment will not come upon them from where they are unaware?"
  16,46,"Or that He will not seize them<i class=""s"">(suddenly) </i>during their movement so that they cannot thwart<i class=""s"">(Him) </i>?"
  16,47,"Or that He will not seize them gradually? Yet indeed, your Lord is truly Compassionate, Bestowing of mercy."
  16,48,"Have <span class=""h"">they<sup foot_note=""80389"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">not seen</span>all things that Allah has created—their shadows revolving from the right and the left, prostrating to Allah as they shrink away?"
  16,49,"And to Allah prostrates whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth of every treading creature, as well as the angels, and they do not act arrogantly—"
  16,50,"fearing their Lord above them and doing whatever they are commanded."
  16,51,"And Allah has said: “Do<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>not take two gods; He is but One God, so of Me{1}alone be in awe.”",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 1st  person.
  16,52,"And to Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth, and religion is His forever. Are you then mindful of anyone other than Allah?"
  16,53,"And whatever blessing you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>have is from Allah, then when harm touches you, it is to Him that you cry for help."
  16,54,"Then when He lifts off harm from you, a group of you associate<i class=""s"">(others) </i>with their Lord,"
